<TITLE> 4 buried in Bandarban, killed by elephant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, July 11 (bdnews24.com) - Three brothers and a sister buried their parents and siblings in Bandarban Friday, after they were killed by a wild elephant in the previous night. The incident occurred at Rajapara hill, adjacent to the Tirer Deba area, in Fanshiakhali union. Acting union parishad chairman of Fanshiakhali Md Kamaluddin and former UP member Md Bachchu Miah said a wild elephant came down to Tirer Deba area at about 11pm Thursday. The elephant rampaged the house of 50 year-old day labourer Syed Alam. Syed Alam's family woke up and tried to flee. But Alam, his wife Zarina Khatun (40), son Jobaer (10) and daughter Kulsum Ara (4) were trampled to death under the feet of the wild elephant. They died on the spot. Another day labourer Anwar was injured in the incident. The UP chairman, member, upazila nirbahi officer Kamrul Hasan and police officer-in-charge Abul Kalam visited the spot. The UNO gave Tk 2,000 to the three surviving sons and daughter of Syed Alam and assured them of more assistance. bdnews2
